Hi,

We are using the BIND name server and we are experiencing a problem
in using gethostbyname().

Whenever a host has more than one Internet address, the gethostbyname()
returns only the first one which may not be the right one.  One way to fix
the problem is to put a list of preferred networks to match on in the
routine as recently done at Purdue.  However, it seems to be impractical
to me since I found that brl-tgr.arpa having the Internet addresses,
192.5.21.4 and 192.5.23.4; both addresses are in unfamiliar networks and
only one address that is usable.  There would be more of hosts like this
one.

I also noticed that the first Internet address found in NIC host table or
returned from a name server at SRI-NIC or USC-ISIB is usually the right
one for us.  However, when the adresses are in cache of BIND name
server, it returns the addresses in reverse order.

Is there any specific order in putting in Internet addresses in a name
server database and returning them especially at the root name servers?
Is there a better algorithm in choosing an Internet address without
trying it?  Do I miss something?

Voradesh Yenbut
Computer Science Department
University of Washington
ARPA: yenbut@uw-oahu.arpa
UUCP: uw-beaver!uw-oahu!yenbut

